# 7. 最後の日

Crew Member: That's all for this morning! We'll resume shooting after lunch!
Rui: (Our morning shoot's already over...)
Rui: (After lunch, we'll be doing that scene again.)
???: I'd try to rethink this scene with Reki Bakuno in mind.
Rui: (With those words in mind, I rewatched all the old footage I could.)
Rui: (Not just for this film... I even asked Mr. Kato to send over footage of any of Bakuno's previous stage performances.)
Rui: (Unfortunately... I still wasn't able to find an answer.)
Rui: (What are we missing? What did he see...?)
Rin: <Rui, is something wrong?>
Rui: Rin...? What brings you here?
Rin: <You haven't really slept since yesterday, so I came to see how you were doing.>
Rin: <Wait, those bags under your eyes! You really should get some rest if you can!>
Rui: You got me.
Rui: But I'm okay. More importantly, I need to figure out what we're missing.
Tsukasa: There you are, Rui! Oh, Rin's here as well.
Rui: All of you...
Rin: <Huh? What's with the big bag, Tsukasa?>
Tsukasa: Heh heh heh. It's full of our lunches, including yours, Rui!
Rui: Oh, including me...?
Nene: We're heading over to the airport to shoot that scene again after lunch, right? So, we think you should eat while you can.
Emu: Having some yummy food should help you come up with really good ideas!
Tsukasa: Which is why we brought you a hearty barbeque lunch! This was the last one they had, so you should consider yourself lucky!
Rui: Yes, I agree that I should provide myself with some nourishment. Thank you, everyone.
Rin: <Oh, you guys' lunches are all different!>
Rin: <Nene's got a Japanese-style lunch, Emu's looks Western, and Tsukasa's having some sandwiches!>
Emu: Hehe. It's so great how we get to choose our lunches like this!
Tsukasa: Good point. Normally, you would expect them to provide the same meal for everyone.
Tsukasa: But considering how many people are working on this film, there must be a wide range of preferences, and they've given us a few choices to meet everyone's needs!
Rui: To meet everyone's needs...
Emu: Oh, I just thought of something amazing!
Emu: Getting to choose our lunches is really nice! But wouldn't it be even nicer if we could choose what's inside?!
Nene: What do you mean?
Emu: Take Rui's lunch for example. It's a big barbeque lunch that's chock-full of meat and vegetables, right?
Emu: But Rui hates vegetables. So, wouldn't it make him happier if he were allowed to have no veggies?!
Rui: ...!
Emu: As for me, I'd want to have lots and lots more veggies instead of meat!
Nene: It wouldn't be much of a “barbeque” lunch if you did that. Also, you're basically talking about a buffet.
Rui: (Individualized lunches based on each person's wants and needs...)
Rui: Now I see... That's what we've been missing.
Emu: Rui?
Nene: Did you figure something out?
Rui: Yes. I think I understand why that scene didn't go as well as planned.
Rin: <What?>
Rui: I need to go talk to Mr. Ohara. The rest of you keep eating.
Nene: Hey, wait a—
Nene: *Sigh* There he goes...
Ohara: ...is how I'd like you to do this scene now.
Reki: I see...
Rui: Pardon the interruption, you two.
Ohara: You look like you're out of breath. Is something wrong?
Rui: No, it's about that one scene.
Rui: I think I know what you need to do in order for it to go the way you want.
Reki: What...?! You also had an idea?
Rui: Huh? Also?
Ohara: Yes, I was just discussing my new plan for it with Bakuno.
Ohara: It hit me last night. My friend said he'd rethink the scene to fit Reki Bakuno better, but I thought I'd been doing that up to this point.
Ohara: But further editing what we had didn't give me the answer. Which meant that the problem didn't lie there.
Rui: The problem was the screenplay...
Ohara: Looks like we landed on the same answer.
Ohara: This screenplay is based on the original novel. As such, the lines for each character are more or less all taken straight from it.
Rui: Right. In particular, the climax scene is completely faithful to the dialogue in the book.
Ohara: Exactly. Unfortunately, that dialogue is intended to have maximum impact when read as a part of a novel.
Ohara: In other words... It won't necessarily translate well over to film.
Rui: Yes, but... These lines aren't bad or anything. This scene still works with them in place.
Rui: We may not have run into any problems if we were working with a different cast. However...
Rui: Because Bakuno is playing Katsuyuki, there has to be a better way to do this scene.
Ohara: Precisely.
Rui: So, as important as it is to stay faithful to the original story, the lines for this scene need to suit Bakuno's style better.
Rui: They need to be rewritten in order to allow him to put his skills to full use.
Ohara: Oh...?
Ohara: Haha. I see... Even you decided to stop there.
Reki: Mr. Ohara?
Ohara: That won't be enough, Kamishiro. I'm thinking about going even further.
Rui: What...?
Ohara: Credit where credit's due, you did better than most would in your situation. I commend you for that.
Ohara: But I'd be out of a job if a filmmaking novice like you managed to come up with the same answer as me.
Reki: U-Um, so...
Ohara: It's time to show all you youngsters.
Ohara: You're going to see what Tomomi Ohara is really capable of.
